    "Using this saved z 0 bypasses the inversion step and yields strong detectability, which is comparable to that reported in the original TabWak paper.",
    "But this approach is impractical in real-world detection where the ground-truth z 0 is unavailable.GLW.",
    "We set the number of \"green list\" intervals to m = 5.",
    "Since GLW was originally designed for tabular data with continuous density functions, we introduce a minor modification to extend it to mixed-type tabular data.",
    "Specifically, for entries with non-zero decimal components, we directly apply the standard method proposed in [11]."
